# Gemini skills (piii)

## Mandatory: use skills to close knowledge gaps

This repo vendors Agent Skills under `.agents/skills/`. When working on Gemini-powered features, you MUST load and follow the relevant skill before implementing.

### Gemini Interactions API (required)

When implementing or modifying any of the following:
- Gemini SDK usage (`@google/genai`, `@ai-sdk/google`)
- tool/function calling orchestration
- structured output / schema-guided generation
- multi-turn chat / stateful flows
- streaming responses (SSE)
- background execution / long-running research tasks
- any Gemini-related API routes or provider wrappers

You MUST read:
- `.agents/skills/gemini-interactions-api/SKILL.md`

Then follow its guidance, and fetch the official docs it references when exact API details matter:
- `https://ai.google.dev/gemini-api/docs/interactions.md.txt`
- `https://ai.google.dev/static/api/interactions.openapi.json`

## Enterprise API constraints (do not regress)

When exposing HTTP endpoints:
- Preserve **OpenAI-compatible** request/response shapes and auth per `.cursorrules`.
- Use **Zod** for request/response validation.
- Use **202 + job state machine** for tasks expected to exceed ~5 seconds (Trigger.dev where appropriate).
- Do not add new dependencies without checking the existing stack and getting explicit permission if needed.

## Image generation note

If the work involves **native Gemini image generation/editing**, also apply:
- `.cursor/rules/nano-banana-image-generation.mdc`
- `docs/integrations/nano-banana-gemini-image.md`

